                <head>221. Telegram 1625 to London<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d221fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/9–1455. Confidential; Priority.
                        Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MWP_1">McConaughy</persName>; cleared by
                            <persName corresp="#p_RWS_1">Robertson</persName>. Repeated Priority to
                        Geneva for <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName> as telegram 773.
                        The time of transmission is illegible.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1955-09-22">September 22, 1955</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d221-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d221-1"/>
                <p>1625. Your 1034. Department considers that under Agreed Announcement, <persName
                        corresp="#p_OC_1">O’Neill</persName> should have access to detained
                    Americans if they are not given unimpeded access to <persName corresp="#p_OC_1"
                        >O’Neill</persName>. Imprisoned Americans in special situation where they
                    unable exercise their rights under Agreed Announcement unless PRC provides
                    special facilities for information and communication. Good faith on part of PRC
                    in implementation Agreed Announcement calls for extraordinary treatment these
                    unfortunate persons. PRC has particular responsibility to these persons made
                    helpless by its action. Repeat priority direct to <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1"
                        >Johnson</persName> Geneva any information from Foreign Office re provisions
                    made by PRC for <persName corresp="#p_OC_1">O’Neill</persName> to perform agreed
                    function.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HH_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
